    "body": "## Summary\nThe backend already exposes deployment create, restart, logs, metrics, and event-history routes, but the CLI/SDK/docs still lag the live surface and leave deployment workflows partially undiscoverable or unsupported.\n\n## Why This Matters\n- deployment lifecycle is now a real product surface and should be consistent across server, clients, and docs\n- stale docs and missing client parity create unnecessary support load and broken expectations\n- this is one of the clearest remaining contract-drift pockets after the agent-route parity work\n\n## Evidence\n- `src/api/routes/deployments.py:148`\n- `src/api/routes/deployments.py:252`\n- `src/api/routes/deployments.py:299`\n- `src/api/routes/deployments.py:342`\n- `src/api/routes/deployments.py:367`\n- `cli/commands/deploy.py:13`\n- `sdk/mutx/deployments.py:30`\n- `docs/api/deployments.md:7`\n- `docs/api/deployments.md:9`\n- `docs/api/index.md:20`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- CLI exposes supported deployment operations or docs explicitly mark the intentional omissions\n- SDK adds truthful deployment event-history support and matches live payloads\n- deployment docs match the real route set and current create-path behavior\n- add focused contract coverage for create, restart, events, logs, and metrics\n\n## Notes\nThis is related to the broader route-alignment work, but it remains materially open after the current agent-focused parity PRs.\n",
