    "body": "## Summary\nThe helper scripts and repo guidance still assume root-level Compose files, but the actual Docker Compose definitions live under `infrastructure/docker/`, leaving the documented local bootstrap path broken.\n\n## Why This Matters\n- the repo should have one truthful local stack entrypoint that works from a fresh checkout\n- broken bootstrap scripts push contributors into manual path patching and stale docs\n- this keeps local-first validation from being trustworthy\n\n## Evidence\n- `scripts/dev.sh:8`\n- `scripts/dev.sh:64`\n- `scripts/setup.sh:21`\n- `scripts/setup.sh:24`\n- `infrastructure/docker/docker-compose.yml:1`\n- `AGENTS.md:44`\n- `scripts/setup.sh:33`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- one supported local bootstrap command works from repo root\n- helper scripts reference the real Compose file paths explicitly\n- docs and repo guidance point to the same canonical entrypoint\n- failure messages explain missing Docker or env prerequisites clearly\n\n## Notes\nThis is adjacent to `#96` because it improves truthful local validation, but it is a concrete local bootstrap break rather than generic CI-lane cleanup.\n",
