    "body": "## Summary\nThe SDK exposes `MutxAsyncClient`, but several resource modules still call `httpx.AsyncClient` methods without `await`, so the advertised async surface is still broadly misleading outside the narrow ClawHub fix already in flight.\n\n## Why This Matters\n- async users need a real async contract, not sync wrappers over an async transport\n- partial async support creates hard-to-debug runtime failures in automation code\n- the current API surface encourages usage patterns that are not actually implemented\n\n## Evidence\n- `sdk/mutx/__init__.py:94`\n- `sdk/mutx/__init__.py:105`\n- `sdk/mutx/__init__.py:114`\n- `sdk/mutx/agents.py:89`\n- `sdk/mutx/agents.py:107`\n- `sdk/mutx/deployments.py:32`\n- `sdk/mutx/api_keys.py:48`\n- `sdk/mutx/webhooks.py:48`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- either implement real async resource methods across the exposed SDK surface, or deprecate/remove `MutxAsyncClient`\n- add contract coverage for async agents, deployments, API keys, and webhooks\n- keep README and SDK docs truthful about which async methods are actually supported\n\n## Notes\nThis is related to PR `#100`, but it is materially broader than the ClawHub JSON fix already open there.\n",
